{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZone"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is refcounted and immutable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each time zone has an identifier (for example, ‘Europe\/London’) which is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"platform dependent. See [ctor","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.TimeZone.new"},{"type":"text","text":"] for information on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier formats. The identifier of a time zone can be retrieved using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.TimeZone.get_identifier"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A time zone contains a number of intervals. Each interval has an abbreviation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to describe it (for example, ‘PDT’), an offset to UTC and a flag indicating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if the daylight savings time is in effect during that interval. A time zone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"always has at least one interval — interval 0. Note that interval abbreviations","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are not the same as time zone identifiers (apart from ‘UTC’), and cannot be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed to [ctor"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every UTC time is contained within exactly one interval, but a given"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"local time may be contained within zero, one or two intervals (due to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incontinuities associated with daylight savings time)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An interval may refer to a specific period of time (eg: the duration"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of daylight savings time during 2010) or it may refer to many periods","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of time that share the same properties (eg: all periods of daylight"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"savings time).  It is also possible (usually for political reasons)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that some properties (like the abbreviation) change between intervals"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without other properties changing."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","isActive":true},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"TimeZone","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TimeZone","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TimeZone","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib8TimeZoneC","symbolKind":"class"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezone"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(_:)-3m8y2","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(_:)-6hi6j","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(_:)-8wflv","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(_:)-9sndc","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(_:)-fwfq","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\